label.value: Public Health Applications Research

value.value: Involvement of the public health community (i.e., state and local health departments) in the development of initiatives and programs for cancer risk reduction, and cancer prevention and control.  Primary interest is in 1) research on interventions in cancer control in public health settings and 2) the dissemination and application of research findings among public health agencies and professionals.

label.value: Position Effect Trial

value.value: A type of trial designed to evaluate the effect of body position during and/or after administration of the investigational product.

label.value: Swallowing Function Trial

value.value: A type of trial designed to evaluate the effect of the investigational product on the physiologic act of swallowing.

label.value: Usability Testing Study

value.value: A type of study designed to evaluate the user experience with a product.

label.value: Exclusion Criteria

value.value: Elements of a personal medical history which would prevent an individual from participating in a specific clinical trial.

label.value: Water Effect Trial

value.value: A type of trial designed to evaluate the effects of water on investigational product safety and/or efficacy.

label.value: Anatomical Location of Interest

value.value: The identification of an anatomical location that may contain a tumor, lesion or site of disease, and is part of the assessment of the response to the therapeutic intervention.

label.value: Measurable Tumor Indicator

value.value: An indication as to whether a measurable tumor is present.

label.value: Non-Target Indicator

value.value: An indication as to whether a non-target tumor, lesion, or site of disease is present.

label.value: Fibrotic Lesion Indicator

value.value: An indication as to whether a fibrotic lesion is present.

label.value: Cardiovascular Lesion Indicator

value.value: An indication as to whether a cardiovascular lesion is present.

label.value: Milligram Per Kilogram Per Week

value.value: A dose calculation unit expressed in milligram(s) per kilogram per period of time equal to seven days.

label.value: Drink Dosing Unit

value.value: A dosing measurement based on the drink unit.

label.value: Degree Per Millimeter

value.value: A unit of rotation expressed as the number of degrees per unit of length equal to one millimeter.

label.value: Square Millisecond

value.value: A unit of time which is equal to one thousandth of a second squared.

label.value: Progesterone Receptor Status

value.value: Indicates the progesterone receptor level measured in a primary tumor or in metastases. (>=10 is positive if measured in fmols/mg cytosol protein; Otherwise use institutional standards)

label.value: Per Millisecond

value.value: A unit of time, which is equal to the reciprocal of one thousandth of a second.

label.value: Electrochemiluminescence Unit

value.value: A unit for measuring concentration or/and reactivity of a test substance as defined in the literature reference standard for the particular quantitative electrochemiluminescent method.

label.value: Genomic Equivalents per Milliliter

value.value: A unit of concentration defined as the number of genomic equivalents per milliliter.

label.value: Genomic Equivalents

value.value: A unit defined as the number of whole organism genomes in a sample.

label.value: D-Dimer Unit

value.value: A unit of measure for the concentration of fibrin degradation products in a sample, calculated based upon the mass of D-dimers contained within that sample.

label.value: Micrograms DDU Per Liter

value.value: A unit of equivalent concentration equal to the number of micrograms of D-dimer per unit volume equal to one liter.
